25|$|An {{equilateral}} triangle has all sides the same length. An {{equilateral triangle}} {{is also a}} <b>regular</b> <b>polygon</b> with all angles measuring 60°.|$|E
25|$|The {{area of a}} <b>regular</b> <b>polygon</b> is {{half its}} {{perimeter}} times the apothem (where the apothem is {{the distance from the}} center to the nearest point on any side).|$|E
25|$|Uniform: vertex-transitive {{and every}} {{face is a}} <b>regular</b> <b>polygon,</b> i.e., it is regular, quasi-regular or semi-regular. A uniform dual is face-transitive and has regular vertices, but is not {{necessarily}} vertex-transitive.|$|E
